Copilot said: I'll help you run this TypeScript project
I'll help you run this TypeScript project (Project_Scholarship) on Windows 10. Here's a step-by-step guide:

Prerequisites Installation:
bash
# 1. Install Node.js and npm
- Download Node.js from https://nodejs.org/ (LTS version recommended)
- During installation, make sure to check "Automatically install the necessary tools"

# 2. Verify installations in Command Prompt:
node --version
npm --version
Project Setup:
bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/ibrahim200806/Project_Scholarship.git
cd Project_Scholarship

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install
Running the Application:
bash
# Start the development server
npm run dev

# The application should start and be available at:
# http://localhost:5173
Building for Production:
bash
# Create production build
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview
Additional Tips:

Make sure you have a modern web browser installed (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
If you encounter any Node.js related errors:
bash
# Clear npm cache
npm cache clean --force

# Delete node_modules and reinstall
rm -rf node_modules
npm install
If you get any TypeScript compilation errors:
bash
# Install TypeScript globally
npm install -g typescript
Project Structure:

The project uses React.js 18 with TypeScript
Styling is done with Tailwind CSS
Routes are handled by React Router
State management uses Context API
Environment Requirements:

Node.js 18 or higher
npm (comes with Node.js)
Modern web browser with JavaScript enabled
The application includes features like:

User authentication with OTP verification
Profile management with document upload
Scholarship matching system
Dashboard with personalized feeds
Multilingual support (Tamil/English)
After starting the development server, the application will be accessible through your web browser at http://localhost:5173. Make sure all services (like authentication and database) are properly configured before running the application.

Let me know if you encounter any specific errors or need additional help!
